The paper deals with transfer learning using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and focuses on improving the generalization ability of machine learning feature representations to estimate human-like cognition and behavior. This topic is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning to model human perception and behavior, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper emphasizes the individual variability in perception, which is a key aspect of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
